oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: C.C. Thompson General Store
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: C.C. Thompson General Store, located on Duplex Road. People are sitting outside on the porch of the store.

Clinton C. Thompson (1878-1952) was a groceryman and farmer and native of the Duplex community and of Thompsons Station. The Thompson Store is a property in Duplex, Tennessee that was listed on the National Register of Historic Places (NRHP) in 1988. and delisted in 2009. It is a one-story, wood-frame building dating from approximately 1890-1900 that was the general store and post office of the crossroads community of Duplex into the mid-1900s.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
